---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Property Management Software Migration Checklist | Free PDF" description="Free step-by-step checklist for migrating to new property management software. Avoid data loss and downtime. Includes timeline, data mapping, and testing phases." canonical="https://www.propertymanagepro.com/resources/migration-checklist/" lastUpdated="June 14, 2026">
  <h1>Property Management Software Migration Checklist</h1>
  <p>Switching property management platforms? Follow this step-by-step checklist to ensure a smooth migration without data loss, payment interruptions, or compliance gaps.</p>

  <div class="affiliate-disclosure">
    This checklist is free to use and share. No registration required.
  </div>

  <div class="quick-verdict">
    <h3>Migration at a Glance</h3>
    <p><strong>Typical timeline:</strong> 4-12 weeks depending on portfolio size and platform complexity.<br />
    <strong>Key risk:</strong> Data mapping errors (reserve balances, owner ledgers, violation history).<br />
    <strong>Cost:</strong> Most vendors include migration support in onboarding; budget 10-20 hours of staff time.</p>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2>Phase 1: Planning (Week 1-2)</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Identify stakeholders (board, manager, accountant, IT)</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Audit current software — what's working, what's broken</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Define must-have features vs nice-to-have</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Set budget (software + migration + training)</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Create data inventory of everything to migrate</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Request migration timelines from top <a href="/category/hoa/">3 vendors</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Phase 2: Data Preparation (Week 2-3)</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Export owner/resident database (names, addresses, contact info)</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Export financial data: general ledger, AR, AP, bank transactions</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Export violation and ARC request history (last 3 years minimum)</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Export governing documents, CC&Rs, rules & regulations</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Reserve study reports and current balance</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Vendor contracts and insurance certificates</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Clean up data: deduplicate, correct errors, fill gaps</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Phase 3: Setup & Configuration (Week 3-5)</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Create account structure (communities, units, ledgers)</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Configure chart of accounts matching current setup</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Set up fee schedules, late fees, and payment rules</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Configure violation templates, ARC forms, and notice templates</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Set up user roles and permissions</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Configure bank integration and payment gateways</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Set up QuickBooks/accounting sync</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Customize owner/resident portal branding</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Phase 4: Data Migration (Week 4-6)</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Import owner/resident database (verify completeness)</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Import beginning balances (AR, reserve fund, operating account)</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Upload governing documents to document repository</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Migrate open work orders and maintenance requests</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Import vendor directory and insurance records</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Run data validation — spot-check 20% of records</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Phase 5: Testing & Training (Week 5-7)</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Board/management team hands-on training session</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Staff training: daily operations, reporting, end-of-month close</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Test payment processing — run $1 test transactions</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Test QuickBooks/accounting sync — reconcile balances</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Test resident portal — create test owner account</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Test email/communication templates</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Run parallel systems for 1-2 weeks (old + new)</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Phase 6: Go Live (Week 7-8)</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Communicate go-live date to all owners/residents</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Send portal activation emails</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Switch payment processing to new system</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Deactivate old system (keep read-only access for 90 days)</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Monitor first payment cycle closely</div>
      <div class="checklist-item"><input type="checkbox" /> Schedule 30/60/90 day check-ins with vendor support</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Common Migration Pitfalls to Avoid</h2>
    <div style="background: #fef2f2; border-left: 4px solid #dc2626; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
      <ul style="margin: 0;">
        <li><strong>Incomplete data mapping:</strong> Know exactly which fields map between old and new systems</li>
        <li><strong>Skipping parallel run:</strong> Always run both systems for at least one payment cycle</li>
        <li><strong>No rollback plan:</strong> Document exactly how to revert if something goes wrong</li>
        <li><strong>Underestimating training:</strong> Budget 2-3x more training time than vendors estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Ignoring historical reporting:</strong> Ensure old reports remain accessible for audits</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <h3>Ready to Switch?</h3>
    <p>Compare the top platforms and find one that makes migration easy.</p>
    <a href="/compare/buildium-vs-appfolio/" class="cta-btn-large">Compare Buildium vs AppFolio</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .checklist { margin: 1.5rem 0; }
  .checklist-item { padding: 0.75rem; background: white; border: 1px solid #e5e7eb; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .checklist-item input[type="checkbox"] { width: 20px; height: 20px; accent-color: #059669; flex-shrink: 0; }
</style>
